        <hr>
        <div class="row c24-vacancy-details">
            <div class="col">
                <h1 class=" text-left  mt-0">Vacancy Details</h1>
                        <p class="mb-15">Employer: <a href="/"><strong>Hire Resolve</strong></a></p>


                    <div class="v-descrip">
                        <p>A well-established national healthcare and pharmaceutical services organization focused on delivering innovative pharmacy and healthcare solutions across South Africa, is currently seeking a <strong>Senior BI Project Coordinator</strong> to join its team in Umhlanga.</p><p>This role is ideal for an experienced project coordination professional with a strong background in Business Intelligence (BI), data-driven initiatives, stakeholder engagement, and cross-functional project delivery. The successful candidate will play a key role in coordinating BI projects, ensuring timelines are met, resources are effectively managed, and business objectives are achieved.</p><h3>Responsibilities</h3><ul class="bullet-list"><li>Coordinate and oversee Business Intelligence projects from initiation through completion.</li><li>Monitor project timelines, milestones, budgets, and deliverables.</li><li>Collaborate with BI analysts, developers, business stakeholders, and management teams.</li><li>Facilitate project meetings and provide regular progress reports.</li><li>Track project risks, issues, and dependencies, ensuring timely resolution.</li><li>Assist with resource planning and project scheduling.</li><li>Ensure compliance with organizational project management standards and methodologies.</li><li>Support data reporting, dashboard implementation, and analytics initiatives.</li><li>Maintain project documentation and governance records.</li><li>Drive continuous improvement within BI project processes.</li></ul><h3>Requirements</h3><ul class="bullet-list"><li>Diploma or Degree in Information Systems, Business Management, Project Management, Computer Science, or a related field.</li><li>Minimum 4–6 years' experience in project coordination or project management.</li><li>Experience working within Business Intelligence, data analytics, reporting, or related environments.</li><li>Strong understanding of project management methodologies and best practices.</li><li>Proficiency in Microsoft Office Suite, particularly Excel and PowerPoint.</li><li>Experience with project management tools and reporting platforms.</li><li>Excellent communication, stakeholder management, and organizational skills.</li><li>Strong analytical and problem-solving abilities.</li><li>Ability to manage multiple projects and priorities simultaneously.</li><li>Project Management certification will be advantageous.</li></ul><h3>Benefits<br></h3><p>Contact Hire Resolve for you next career-changing move.</p><ul dir="auto"><li>Salary: Market related (Negotiable) depending on experience and experience.</li></ul><ul dir="auto"><li>Apply for this role today, contact Lisa Meyer at Hire Resolve or on LinkedIn</li></ul><ul dir="auto"><li>You can also visit the Hire Resolve website: hireresolve.us or email us your CV: <a>manufacturing@hireresolve.za.com</a></li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>
                    </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <hr>


    





